Red Carpet Apartments - 10:30-11:00

Legion Park - 11:30-12:00

Meal Pick-up: The child receiving the "grab & go" meal must be present. Once meals are picked up, individuals must leave the distribution site and not congregate.

All students will receive that day's lunch as well as the next day's breakfast in one bag at pickup.

Fairview Band & Band Booster Programs
December 9, 2019 at 3:38 PM Â·

Tomorrow evening, Tuesday, December 10th, 6:30pm please join us at the arts and education building for the Fairview Public Schools Christmas Band Concert.and coronation ceremony.

You will want to be in your seats early as we will have a slideshow of some of what the kids have been doing so far this year.

The 5th grade beginner band will start the evening followed by the 6th grade band. The 7th and 8th will perform together. We are trying something new this year. We will be crowning a band king and queen between the junior high and high school performances.

Thank you for the support you have extended to us this year. Let us show you how hard the kids have been working. Come out and support the band programs.

post_text: Congratulations to these seniors!
shared_text:
Fairview Oklahoma Police Department is feeling proud.
November 1, 2019 at 3:30 PM Â·

*************** SPECIAL ANNOUNCEMENT ***************

As some of you may have heard, earlier this year, the Fairview City Council approved our request to start a Scholarship Program for Fairview High School Seniors!

We have designed and created a Scholarship Program that we feel will be immensely beneficial to the Student Participants, our citizens, and our community.

The program, titled "Operation BLUE SHADOW" will immerse the participants into the entire operation of our Municipal Government. They will experience the daily routines of each and every department, gain new insight and perspective into the operation of each employee's role, and how we work harmoniously together as one teamâ€¦
